[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1m# Vector Search in Distillery\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  The team chose \u001b[1mDuckDB with HNSW indexes\u001b[0m for vector similarity\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  search \u001b[2m[Entry e7a3f1b2]\u001b[0m. This decision was driven by three factors:\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1m1.\u001b[0m \u001b[1mSingle-file storage\u001b[0m — DuckDB keeps the entire knowledge base\r\n     in one file, making backups and portability trivial.\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1m2.\u001b[0m \u001b[1mNo network hops\u001b[0m — unlike hosted vector databases, queries\r\n     run in-process with zero latency overhead.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[1m3.\u001b[0m \u001b[1mNative cosine similarity\u001b[0m — the VSS extension provides\r\n     HNSW-indexed cosine distance out of the box.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m┌─────────┬──────────────┬──────────┬─────────┬───────────┐\u001b[0m\r\n"]
